                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-700">What is Tailwind CSS?</h2>
                <p class="mb-4">Tailwind CSS is a utility-first CSS framework that provides low-level utility classes to build custom designs without writing CSS from scratch.</p>
                <div class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-4 text-white">
                    <p class="font-mono text-sm">
                        <span class="text-blue-400">// Traditional CSS</span><br>
                        .button {<br>
                        &nbsp;&nbsp;display: inline-block;<br>
                        &nbsp;&nbsp;padding: 0.5rem 1rem;<br>
                        &nbsp;&nbsp;background-color: #3b82f6;<br>
                        &nbsp;&nbsp;color: white;<br>
                        &nbsp;&nbsp;border-radius: 0.25rem;<br>
                        }<br><br>
                        <span class="text-blue-400">// Tailwind equivalent</span><br>
                        &lt;button class="inline-block px-4 py-2 bg-blue-500 text-white rounded"&gt;<br>
                        &nbsp;&nbsp;Click me<br>
                        &lt;/button&gt;
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>

